The first note to play on the Trombone is 
Bb. (pronounced “B Flat”)  Bb is shown here on the staff.  The flat symbol is placed before the note.  Later on we will discuss flats in more detail.
Try the challenge after completing the exercises.  The Challenge will give you a new and never before seen exercise to make sure you are reading the music!

Let’s try some exercises using Bb.  Be sure to remember the
rhythms discussed in the Intro To Music Notation.
